Here are some thoughts about why I want to perform the action. The miscompilation persists because GVN still performs dominated-use replacements in the equality propagation loop without considering MD_range differences between LHS and RHS. I will insert a guard right before replaceDominatedUsesWithIf calls to skip replacements when both LHS and RHS are Instructions and their MD_range metadata differs. This will prevent turning a well-defined value into poison in cases like differing ctpop range metadata.

```bash
python3 - << 'PY'
import re
path = 'llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp'
s = open(path).read()

anchor = 'unsigned NumReplacements =\n          DominatesByEdge\n              ? replaceDominatedUsesWithIf(LHS, RHS, *DT, Root,\n                                           canReplacePointersCallBack)\n              : replaceDominatedUsesWithIf(LHS, RHS, *DT, Root.getStart(),\n                                           canReplacePointersCallBack);'
guard = '''unsigned NumReplacements = 0;
      // Guard against unsafe replacements when MD_range differs.
      if (isa<Instruction>(LHS) && isa<Instruction>(RHS)) {
        auto *LHSI = cast<Instruction>(LHS);
        auto *RHSI = cast<Instruction>(RHS);
        MDNode *LHSRange = LHSI->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range);
        MDNode *RHSRange = RHSI->getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range);
        if (LHSRange && LHSRange != RHSRange) {
          // Skip replacements to avoid introducing poison via mismatched range MD.
          NumReplacements = 0;
        } else {
          NumReplacements =
              DominatesByEdge
                  ? replaceDominatedUsesWithIf(LHS, RHS, *DT, Root,
                                               canReplacePointersCallBack)
                  : replaceDominatedUsesWithIf(LHS, RHS, *DT, Root.getStart(),
                                               canReplacePointersCallBack);
        }
      } else {
        NumReplacements =
            DominatesByEdge
                ? replaceDominatedUsesWithIf(LHS, RHS, *DT, Root,
                                             canReplacePointersCallBack)
                : replaceDominatedUsesWithIf(LHS, RHS, *DT, Root.getStart(),
                                             canReplacePointersCallBack);
      }'''
if anchor in s:
    s = s.replace(anchor, guard)
    open(path,'w').write(s)
    print("Inserted MD_range guard before replaceDominatedUsesWithIf in GVN equality propagation.")
else:
    print("Anchor not found; no changes made.")
PY
```

